fields.name: iTOW
fields.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch. See section iTOW timestamps in the integration manual for details.

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x00 for this version)

fields.name: numSigs
fields.description: Number of signals

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: gnssId
fields.description: GNSS identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: sigId
fields.description: New style signal identifier (see Signal Identifiers)

fields.name: freqId
fields.description: Only used for GLONASS: This is the frequency slot + 7 (range from 0 to 13)

fields.name: prRes
fields.description: Pseudorange residual

fields.name: cno
fields.description: Carrier-to-noise density ratio (signal strength)

fields.name: qualityInd
fields.description: Signal quality indicator: 0 = no signal, 1 = searching signal, 2 = signal acquired, 3 = signal detected but unusable, 4 = code locked and time synchronized, 5, 6, 7 = code and carrier locked and time synchronized

fields.name: corrSource
fields.description: Correction source: 0 = no corrections, 1 = SBAS corrections, 2 = BeiDou corrections, 3 = RTCM2 corrections, 4 = RTCM3 OSR corrections, 5 = RTCM3 SSR corrections, 6 = QZSS SLAS corrections, 7 = SPARTN corrections, 9 = CLAS corrections, 10 = LPP OSR corrections, 11 = LPP SSR corrections, 12 = GAL HAS corrections

fields.name: ionoModel
fields.description: Ionospheric model used: 0 = Default delay values, 1 = Klobuchar model transmitted by GPS, 2 = SBAS model, 3 = Klobuchar model transmitted by BeiDou, 4 = NTCM model transmitted by Galileo, 8 = Iono delay derived from dual frequency observations

fields.name: sigFlags
fields.description: Signal related flags

bits.name: health
bits.description: Signal health flag: 0 = unknown, 1 = healthy, 2 = unhealthy

bits.name: prSmoothed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange has been smoothed

bits.name: prUsed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange has been used for this signal

bits.name: crUsed
bits.description: 1 = Carrier range has been used for this signal

bits.name: doUsed
bits.description: 1 = Range rate (Doppler) has been used for this signal

bits.name: prCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: crCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Carrier range corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: doCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Range rate (Doppler) corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: authStatus
bits.description: Authentication status of the navigation data used to compute the satellite's position in current navigation epoch. If the authentication fails, the navigation data is not used so the authentication status in this message can take only two values: 0 = Unknown, 1 = Authenticated. Note that currently the only data authentication function is provided by Galileo Open Service Navigation Message Authentication (OSNMA) protocol for E1 I/NAV message.

fields.description: GNSS identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: sigId
fields.description: New style signal identifier (see Signal Identifiers)

fields.name: freqId
fields.description: Only used for GLONASS: This is the frequency slot + 7 (range from 0 to 13)

fields.name: prRes
fields.description: Pseudorange residual

fields.name: cno
fields.description: Carrier-to-noise density ratio (signal strength)

fields.name: qualityInd
fields.description:
Signal quality indicator:
0 = no signal
1 = searching signal
2 = signal acquired
3 = signal detected but unusable
4 = code locked and time synchronized
5, 6, 7 = code and carrier locked and time synchronized

fields.name: corrSource
fields.description:
Correction source:
0 = no corrections
1 = SBAS corrections
2 = BeiDou corrections
3 = RTCM2 corrections
4 = RTCM3 OSR corrections
5 = RTCM3 SSR corrections
6 = QZSS SLAS corrections
7 = SPARTN corrections
9 = CLAS corrections
10 = LPP OSR corrections
11 = LPP SSR corrections
12 = GAL HAS corrections

fields.name: ionoModel
fields.description:
Ionospheric model used:
0 = Default delay values
1 = Klobuchar model transmitted by GPS
2 = SBAS model
3 = Klobuchar model transmitted by BeiDou
4 = NTCM model transmitted by Galileo
8 = Iono delay derived from dual frequency observations

fields.name: sigFlags
fields.description: Signal related flags

bits.name: health
bits.description:
Signal health flag:
0 = unknown
1 = healthy
2 = unhealthy

bits.name: prSmoothed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange has been smoothed

bits.name: prUsed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange has been used for this signal

bits.name: crUsed
bits.description: 1 = Carrier range has been used for this signal

bits.name: doUsed
bits.description: 1 = Range rate (Doppler) has been used for this signal

bits.name: prCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Pseudorange corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: crCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Carrier range corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: doCorrUsed
bits.description: 1 = Range rate (Doppler) corrections have been used for this signal

bits.name: authStatus
bits.description:
Authentication status of the navigation data used to compute the satellite's position in current navigation epoch. If the authentication fails, the navigation data is not used so the authentication status in this message can take only two values:
0 = Unknown
1 = Authenticated
Note that currently the only data authentication function is provided by Galileo Open Service Navigation Message Authentication (OSNMA) protocol for E1 I/NAV message.
